page.title: 10The White House Museum
page.content:
The White House itself is not the only building of interest. You can also look around the{17th Century coach {house and granary}which houses various traps and items of machinery. There is also a{Cider House,}also constructed in the 17th Century, complete with cider mill and press.
In the{16th Century stable block}is a life size model of a horse and a lady in beautiful riding habit. In front of the White House is the ruin of a {13th Century Dove Cote.
Gardens are numerous, each with a different subject, all relating the development of natural life down the ages. Chemicals have never been used on this six and a half acres of original Saxon Manor.
